definitions.definition: The state or quality of being aggressive .
The propensity of a soil or water to dissolve metal or cement structures.
examples: The aggressiveness of various sulfate salts towards concrete is partly related to solubility.

definitions.definition: The result or product of being aggressive .

main_definition: ( uncountable ) The state or quality of being aggressive .
secondary_definitions: ( uncountable ) The propensity of a soil or water to dissolve metal or cement structures.
( countable ) The result or product of being aggressive .
